# Infrastructure Parser Guide

Parsers translate raw data from external sources (JSON, CSV, etc.) into domain models. They should be stateless and contain no business logic.

Typical structure:
```python
class BankAccountParser:
    def parse_bank_accounts(self, api_response: list[dict]) -> list[KyribaBankAccount]:
        ...
```

Keep parsers lightweight. A real parser might transform API payloads into
domain models without side effects.
